title: Yeovil 2-2 Dag Red: Match Report
text:
Yeovil 2-2 Dag Red: Match Report 10 Oct 2015 16:31:00 
comments Jakub Sokolik fluke caps Yeovil comeback to earn draw with DagenhamYeovil fought back from two goals down to clinch a point in a spirited 2-2 draw at home to fellow strugglers Dagenham.Ryan Bird and Jakub Sokolik earned the Glovers a share of the spoils after first-half strikes from Kane Ferdinand and Frankie Raymond had seemingly left the Daggers on course for victory at Huish Park.After 18 minutes noticeably bereft of spark, the Daggers drew first blood when Ferdinand nodded home, Ashley Chambers producing a good cross to find the midfielder after his earlier shot cannoned off the post.The visitors then doubled their lead two minutes before half-time as Raymond pounced first onto a loose ball to unleash a thunderbolt past Artur Krysiak from 20 yards out.Yeovil pulled a goal back in the 69th minute when Bird headed in Connor Roberts' cross, and seven minutes later they drew level via a huge slice of luck courtesy of Daggers keeper Liam O'Brien, whose punch hit the oblivious Sokolik and rebounded into the net to secure the Glovers a share of the spoils.
